CatDescriptText: Mrs. Anna Flurry, 30-D Midway Dr., Whitaker, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think it justifiable for residents to "put the finger" (notify law enforcement officers) on rackets if they exist in their respective communities?" answer reads: "Yes, I do, because it will make a better place in which to live- especially to raise children."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Anna Flurry, wearing head scarf, dark gloves, and light colored fine houndstooth coat, standing in front of service station, possibly Texaco
